The Hindu Community across the world yesterday celebrated the climax of the annual four day Diwali religious festival with the event being marked by various activities. The festival also known as the Festival of Lights is celebrated to honor Rama-Chandra who is believed to be the incarnation of the Hindu god Vishnu. It is believed that on this day Rama-Chandra returned home after 14 years of exile during which he fought and won the battle against demons and the demon King Ravana. 